> 	How to trace a program which uses threads. gdb is useful for tasks which
> have a single thread of execution. Please let me know of any utility which
> does this.
This is **NOT** a linux-kernel issue.
See 
	
http://sourceware.cygnus.com/gdb/
and keep in mind that the following supports threads:
	- the gdb shipped with redhat 6.1 (4.18+ patches)
	- the current snapshot of gdb (incoming gdb 5.0)
